Subject: ENTS Automation — Sprint Progress Update

Hi [Scrum Master Name],

Please find below a summary of progress made on the ENTS automation workstream this sprint.

1. NR/CISYF End-to-End Regression (TC_13) — Completed
A full end-to-end regression scenario has been automated covering the entire NRCISYF business flow across 23 sections. This includes category selection (A, B, C, A+C, B+C, invalid A+B combinations), all entity types (Individual, Joint Herdowner, Company), document uploads, submission with declaration, Save and Exit, custom institution/qualification paths, invalid file format validation and post-submission correspondence verification.

2. Transfer of Entitlements — All Agent Types Automated (TC_01 to TC_12)
Automation coverage has been completed for all transfer flow combinations including Agent-to-Agent (same and cross-agent), Agent-to-Individual, Agent-to-ETF Partner, Individual-to-Agent, Individual-to-ETF Partner, ETF Partner-to-Agent and ETF Partner-to-Individual. All 12 ENTS transfer test cases have been migrated from the legacy framework into the modernised BDD structure.

3. Self-Healing Recovery Implemented for Submitted Herds
The Apply/Edit dialog step now includes a 95-attempt self-healing recovery loop. When a herd is found in submitted state, the framework automatically re-queries the database, validates a fresh candidate herd and agent, logs out, re-logs in, and retries — without manual intervention.

4. Runtime Database-Driven Test Data
All hardcoded herd numbers and agent usernames have been removed. Test data is now resolved dynamically at runtime from BISS_DATA and BISS_INET via the DBRouter component. The CISYF query has been fixed to prevent ORA-06503 errors by wrapping the PL/SQL function call in a scalar subquery.

5. Angular Datepicker Reliability Fix
A reusable clearAndEnterDate helper has been introduced to reliably handle disabled Angular Material datepicker fields across all three qualification date inputs. The previous approach using clear() was not resetting Angular component state, causing date fields to retain stale values between runs.

6. Staff ENTSCore Verification (TC_15)
A new test case has been implemented that submits an NRCISYF application as an agent and then cross-verifies the submission in ENTSCore as a staff user — covering the end-to-end business journey from portal submission through to back-office visibility.

